  "prompt": "What are the best Indian gaming companies that builds small open world, first-person shooter, 3d games for Ios that you can hire so they can make games for you?",
  "response": "There are several Indian gaming companies with a good reputation for developing high-quality games. While not all may specifically focus on small open-world, first-person shooter, 3D games for iOS, those with a strong background in diverse game development can potentially fulfill such requirements. Here are a few notable companies:\n\n1. **Nazara Technologies**: Known for their wide range of mobile games, Nazara Technologies has experience in developing engaging and interactive games. They are one of the leading mobile game companies in India.\n\n2. **nCore Games**: This company gained popularity with games like FAU-G, a multiplayer action game. They have experience in developing comprehensive and engaging gaming experiences for mobile platforms.\n\n3. **Reliance Games**: Part of the Reliance Entertainment Group, they have developed several successful mobile games and have a strong portfolio that includes various genres.\n\n4. **Octro**: Known for creating social games, Octro has a strong presence in the mobile gaming market. While their focus has been more on multiplayer and social experiences, they have a solid technical base to explore other genres.\n\n5. **99Games**: Based in Udupi, India, 99Games has developed several successful mobile games across different genres, focusing on high production value and engaging gameplay.\n\n6. **Robosoft Technologies**: While primarily a digital solutions company, their gaming division has developed numerous games for iOS and other platforms, demonstrating versatility and expertise in game development.\n\n7. **Games2Win**: This company has a large portfolio of mobile games, many of which have been quite popular. They have experience with various gaming genres and could potentially develop an FPS-3D game.\n\nTo hire them for game development, you would typically reach out through their official websites or professional networks like LinkedIn. It\u2019s important to clearly communicate your project requirements, expected deliverables, and budget to ensure a good fit and successful collaboration.",
